<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-374-142  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 374 142.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Industrial Engineering  June 1989 v21 n6 p52(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>The expanding role of IEs in manufacturing. (industrial engineers)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Engwall, Richard L.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Industrial engineers (IEs) are expanding their role inmanufacturing.andP;  IEs can now be found in manufacturing technology,computer systems, production management, cost accounting, economicanalysis and product line management.andP;  The IE has become theengineering integrationist in the business enterprise, workingwith both a structured methodology and people-sensitive approachto problem-solving.andP;  The education of IEs needs to reflect therapidly changing responsibilities that they now share in theindustrial market.andP;  Their schooling needs to address thesecritical issues and concerns in an integrated multidisciplinedway.andP;  Integration engineers have a systems approach toproblem-solving that enables them to select the most costeffective way towards modernization project selection.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Industrial EngineeringManufacturingManagementIntegrated ApproachEducation.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>